00:57:09.392 --> 00:57:11.828 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Nations may think they are close

00:57:11.828 --> 00:57:14.130 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to solving some of their big problems.”

00:57:15.432 --> 00:57:19.068 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So here’s the question, and it’s understood

00:57:19.068 --> 00:57:21.538 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that it would be asked,

00:57:21.538 --> 00:57:24.674 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Will the faithful slave
be able to at a certain time

00:57:24.674 --> 00:57:27.444 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
say to the brotherhood: “This is it!

00:57:29.379 --> 00:57:31.414 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“This is what we’ve been waiting for.

00:57:31.414 --> 00:57:34.717 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is the ‘peace and security’ prophecy”?

00:57:36.386 --> 00:57:39.255 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, keep this comment in mind

00:57:39.255 --> 00:57:43.993 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from The Watchtower, 2004,
February 1, page 21:

00:57:45.695 --> 00:57:49.399 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Since Bible prophecies
are often fully understood

00:57:49.399 --> 00:57:51.935 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
